  "prompt": "What makeup to wear for red dress?",
  "response": "When choosing makeup to complement a red dress, it's important to strike a balance between bold and subtle to create a harmonious and elegant look. Here are some tips:\n\n### Face:\n- **Foundation**: Select a foundation that matches your skin tone and provides a flawless base.\n- **Blush**: Opt for a soft, neutral blush such as peach or soft pink to add a natural glow without competing with the boldness of the dress.\n\n### Eyes:\n- **Eyeshadow**: Choose neutral shades like taupe, beige, or soft browns. For a more glamorous look, you can add a touch of gold or bronze.\n- **Eyeliner**: Classic black or brown eyeliner works well. You can do a subtle wing for added drama.\n- **Mascara**: Use black mascara to define your lashes, and consider adding false lashes for extra volume.\n\n### Lips:\n- **Red Lipstick**: If you want a classic, bold look, match your lipstick to your dress. Make sure the shade of red complements your skin tone.\n- **Nude Lipstick**: If you prefer a more understated lip, choose a nude lipstick that pairs well with your complexion.\n\n### Highlighter:\n- Apply a subtle highlighter to the high points of your face (cheekbones, bridge of your nose, and the cupid's bow) for a touch of radiance.\n\n### Brows:\n- Keep your brows well-groomed and defined to frame your face.\n\n### Final Touches:\n- Ensure your makeup is well-blended and set with a setting spray to keep it looking fresh all evening.\n\nRemember, the key is to balance your look. If you opt for bold lips, keep your eyes more neutral, and vice versa. This will ensure that your makeup enhances your red dress without overwhelming your overall appearance.",
